 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/src/trusted/desc/nacl_desc_imc.c?r1=3444&amp;r2=3443&amp;pathrev=3444

Allow imc_sendmsg to return EMSGSIZE to indicate that a message is too big to
pass in one call.  This allows a client (e.g., SRPC) to adjust the message size
that it passes to imc_sendmsg.  This is yet another step towards fixing the
pepper string length issue.
